{"id":311613647,"lang":"python3","time":"1 year, 4 months","timestamp":1583962391,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"48 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/311613647/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters","memory":"12.9 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def lengthOfLongestSubstring(self, s: str) -> int:\n        if len(s) == 0:\n            return 0\n        chars = {}\n        # start index of nonduplicate stream\n        start_index = 0\n        # maximum obtained counter\n        max_counter = 0\n        for i in range(len(s)):\n            # non repeating char\n            if s[i] not in chars:\n                chars[s[i]] = i\n            else:\n                # if that is not char from this window\n                if chars[s[i]] < start_index:\n                    # Update char position\n                    chars[s[i]] = i\n                    continue\n                # update the max counter\n                if i - start_index> max_counter:\n                    max_counter = i - start_index\n                # start from the position next to the position where this element appeared last time\n                start_index = chars[s[i]] + 1\n                # Update char position\n                chars[s[i]] = i\n\n        # update the max counter, if the last element makes nonrepeating stream (+1 because last element is not included so far)\n        if i - start_index + 1 > max_counter:\n            max_counter = i - start_index + 1\n        return max_counter","compare_result":"","title_slug":"longest-substring-without-repeating-characters"}
